latestIgtvVideos.title: So proud to be associated with @milliondollarvegan
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
#Repost @milliondollarvegan with @make_repost
・・・
We are extremely grateful to actress @DiganganaSuryavanshi for speaking up about what behaviors cause pandemics and how we can avoid them in the future by adopting a plant-based diet.

Covid-19 has proven that we cannot destroy nature and exploit animals with impunity. All actions have consequences, and consuming animal products facilitates devastating pandemics, animal suffering, habitat loss, ocean pollution, and human suffering too.

Choose vegan for yourself and others. Go to TakePandemicsOffTheMenu.com to learn more. (Link in Bio)

latestIgtvVideos.title: #Repost via @delhi.times Happy Father's Day Papa @neerajsuryavanshi11 ❤️
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
—— @diganganasuryavanshi pens a beautiful poem to express gratitude to her biggest motivator - her dad - for always being there by her side
#HappyFathersDay

You’ve been there! 
From my baby steps
To the skates on my feet 
Early morning jogs
Late night shoots 
The happy times 
And every time I’ve cried 
You’ve been there 
You’ve been there 
My biggest motivator 
And my finest critic 
You’ve said the sweetest things 
And the cruel truths sweetly 
I mark those days
I thought I’d fail
How you laughed at me 
And brushed my fear away 
The twinkle in your eyes
When you see me do well 
But how you come in support 
When I make a mistake 
Won’t say I told you 
Ain’t no blame game 
You’ve been there 
You’ve been there

My exams, shoots, 
Singing sessions 
Or when I write 
You’ve told me just one thing 
How proud you’ve been 
For when I start something new 
You believe in me 
More than I do... you’ve been by my side
No matter what fate decide 
You’ve been there 
You’ve been there 
Like you always say
“Future holds what is does 
But today my princess,
Breathe, laugh and live” 
And I’m so proud 
Of the human you are! 
Values and ethics 
Have been your friends 
Betrayal and lies 
Are far away from you 
Even God can’t be,
The parent you’ve been 
You’d let go off 
Your biggest deal 
Just to make sure 
You’re there for me 
At all times
That I really really need you!
You’ve been there
You’ve been there ! 
No sorries and thank you’s 
Had enough space 
Unity, love, faith 
Always taking over...
Through the bumps 
And the fairytale like high 
You’ve been there
You’ve been there ! 
Dedicated to Papa and Maa on this Father’s Day ❤️ - Digangana Suryavanshi
